            <h3>Focus Trap Example</h3>
            <p>The side drawer implements focus trapping to ensure keyboard navigation stays within the drawer when it's open. This is important for accessibility.</p>

            <h4>Usage:</h4>
<pre><code>&lt;!-- Trigger button --&gt;
&lt;button class="btn" data-drawer-target="my-drawer"&gt;Open Drawer&lt;/button&gt;

&lt;!-- Drawer component --&gt;
&lt;side-drawer id="my-drawer"&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;
    &lt;h2&gt;Drawer Content&lt;/h2&gt;
    &lt;button&gt;Focusable Button 1&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;button&gt;Focusable Button 2&lt;/button&gt;
    &lt;input type="text" placeholder="Focusable input"&gt;
  &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/side-drawer&gt;</code></pre>

            <h4>Configuration Options:</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>
                <code>side</code>
                - Position of the drawer ("left" or "right", defaults to "left")</li>
              <li>
                <code>width</code>
                - Width of the drawer (defaults to "375px")</li>
              <li>
                <code>animation-duration</code>
                - Duration of open/close animation in milliseconds (defaults to 300)</li>
            </ul>

            <h4>Example with Configuration:</h4>
<pre><code>&lt;side-drawer 
  id="my-drawer"
  side="right"
  width="400px"
  animation-duration="400"&gt;
  &lt;div&gt;Drawer content&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/side-drawer&gt;</code></pre>

            <h4>Features:</h4>
            <ul>
              <li>Focus is trapped inside the drawer when open</li>
              <li>Focus returns to the trigger element when closed</li>
              <li>Escape key closes the drawer</li>
              <li>Clicking outside closes the drawer</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="flex gap-4 mt-5">
